Whether or not you believe in reincarnation—and whether or not it is true—is beside the point.What I wish to convey here is a structure:
You are born as a single dog ⚪︎, and you exist within the pattern of “dog”—◇.And when your life comes to an end, ⚪︎ arrives at the door of ◇ that has always been inherent in that life.Your ◇ does not exist outside of you. It has always been within.In that sense, one could say: your ◇ is something that knows everything about you—a presence that could be called God.
